						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall (base-tiers) of the Rāmasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="italic">Durmati (Dundubhi), Āshāḍha,</hi> ba. 2, Thursday, probably equivalent to A.D. 1322, July 1. (in characters of 14th century A.D.)</p>						

						<p>Records the consecration of the god Gōpīnātha by Dharma Rāmaseṭṭi. Another inscription refers to one Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara (name lost).</p>						

